    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In Christi nomine. Notitia brevis commemoracionis seu deliberationis
                        qual(is) et in quorum presencia bonorum hominum se coniuncxerunt id est
                            <persName key="#Prevosts" ref="#people/1296">Rotgildus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Prevosts">prepositus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/15"><orgName
                                key="#Monasteries #Prevosts #Monks #Abbots #Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities"
                                ref="#juridical_persons/47">Nonantule</orgName></placeName> et
                            <persName key="#Monks"><name ref="Ragibertus"
                            >Ragimpert</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Monks">monacho</rs> et <persName
                            key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities" ref="#people/1230"
                            >Raginaldus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities">advocato</rs> ipsius
                        monasterii, una cum <persName
                            key="#Scabini #Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Ragibertus">Raginpertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Scabini">scavino</rs> et advocato <persName key="#Count"
                            ref="#people/663">Waradi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comiti</rs> de <placeName key="#Count" ref="#places/59"
                            >Verona</placeName> agente causa eius, ad <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1109">Sancto Laurencio</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Forests" ref="#places/2492">Ostilia</placeName> prope <rs
                            key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4196">Pado</placeName>. Adesse cum eis
                            <persName key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus" ref="#people/1297">
                            Errardus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">gastaldus</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Agibrandus">Agiprandus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancelarius</rs>, <persName><name ref="Ardingus"
                                >Ardingus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Odalfridus"
                                >Odelfridus</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Ursus"
                                >Urso</name></persName> vel reliq(ui) plures pro causa unde iam
                        inter se vuadicatum habebant in presencia <persName key="#Count"
                            ref="#people/1298">Ragimundi</persName> comiti et <persName
                            key="#Palatine_count #Missus_regis" ref="#people/3903"
                            >Adelgis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Palatine_count">co[mi]s palacii</rs>
                        <rs key="#Missus_regis">missi domni imperatoris</rs>, id est de <rs
                            key="#Forests">silva</rs> illa que dicitur <geogName key="#Forests"
                            ref="#estates/1138">Ostilia</geogName>, ut exinde plenam quartam
                        porcionem dare deberet et medietatem de aliis tribus portionibus a parte
                        ipsius monasterii, quam a parte regia adquisita est per <persName
                            key="#Abbots" ref="#people/49">Anselmum</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbatem</rs>, iusta eius iudicatum sicut iam a parte
                        monast(erii) et inter parte <persName key="#Count" ref="#people/1299"
                            >Hucpaldi</persName> comitis iudicium habuerunt. Et dum ex utraque parte
                        ibi coniuncxissent ceperunt a quarta porcione pertrahere mensura da <rs
                            key="#Fines">fine</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Scabini #Witness #Fines" ref="#places/275"
                            >Mantuana</placeName>, longo ripa de Pado, usque in finem ex silva de
                            <placeName key="#Forests" ref="#places/">Sterano</placeName>, que est
                        sorte de <rs key="#Curtes">domocultile</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/1162">Sancti Laurenti</geogName>, et a
                        sorte Sancti Laurentii usque ad <placeName key="#Canals" ref="#places/"><rs
                                key="#Canals">fossam</rs> que vocatur Regia</placeName>, excepta
                        sorticella illa <persName key="#Count" ref="#people/166">Anselmi</persName>
                        comitis que pertinet de corte sua <placeName key="#Curtes" ref="#places/572"
                                ><geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/1161"
                            >Roverxelle</geogName></placeName>, et de alia partæ similiter
                        mensuraverunt longo fluvio Tartato. Post hec, omnia mensurata et racione
                        facta, sic ipse Ragimpertus scavinus iusta iudicato ipso dedit ipsam plenam
                        quartam porcionem de prefata silva Hostilia et medietatem de aliis tribus
                        porcionibus a parte regia ipsius Rotgildi prepositi et Raginaldo avocatore a
                        parte suprascripti monasterii Nonantule ubi est inter adfines de ipsa quarta
                        porcione da una parte fluvio Pado percurrente et ex alia parte fluvio
                        Tartaro percurrente, da tercia vero parte <placeName key="#Canals"
                            ref="#places/">fossa qui dicitur Olobia</placeName> exiente de Pado
                        percurrente in Tartaro, da quarta autem parte fine Mantuana. Similiter
                        suprascripto Raginperto scavino, iusta iudicato ipso, de aliis tribus
                        partibus hostendit medietatem suprascripto Rotgildo preposito et Raginaldo
                        avocatore a parte monasterii Nonantule ubi est inter adfines de ipsis
                        medietatibus, ex una parte fluvio Pado percurrente et ex alia parte fluvio
                        Tartato, de tercia vero parte sorte Sancti Laurentii, uno capite tenente in
                        Pado, alio capite tenente in Tartaro de quarta autem parte <placeName
                            key="#Canals" ref="#places/">fossa Regia que et Ruza dicitur</placeName>
                        exiente de Pado percurrente in Tartaro, excepta sorte Anselmi comitis. Hoc
                        actum anno domnorum nostrorum Ludovici et Lotharii gloriosissimi imperatores
                        quartodecimo et octavo die veneris quod est undecimo die m(en)s(is)
                        mar(tii), indicione quinta. Feliciter. Ego <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Garibertus">Gariberto</name></persName> filio bone m(emorie)
                            <persName key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus" ref="#people/"
                            >Lanfr(anci)</persName> olim gastaldus in ista causa interfui. <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Anselmus">Anselmus</name></persName> filio
                                <persName><name ref="Ademarius">Odemarii</name></persName> in his
                        actis interfuit. Signum m(anus) <persName key="#Witness #Scabini"><name
                                ref="Liuderadus">Lauderati</name></persName> filio quondam
                                <persName><name ref="Lambertus">Landeberti</name></persName> scavini
                        de Mantua qui ad ipsa investitura interfuit. Signum m(anus) <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Faraldus">Feraldi</name></persName> de
                            <placeName key="#Vici">Cannolas</placeName> qui in his actis <rs
                            key="#Witness">interfuit</rs>. Sign(um) manibus <persName key="#Witness"
                                ><name ref="Teudebrandus">Teoprandi</name></persName> de ipso <rs
                            key="#Vici">vico</rs> qui interfuit. Signum m(anus) <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Leontius">Lionio</name></persName> de
                            <placeName>Riparia</placeName> qui in actis interfuit. Signum m(anus)
                            <persName key="#Witness #Alemannus"><name ref="Aribaldus"
                                >Arimpaldi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Alemannus">Alamanni</rs> qui in his interfuit. Signum m(anus)
                            <persName key="#Witness #Salian"><name ref="Giselbertus"
                                >Giselperti</name></persName> filio <persName><name ref="Adelpertus"
                                >Adolperto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Salian">Franci</rs> qui in his actis interfuit. Signum m(anus)
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Martinus">Martini</name></persName>
                        filio quondam <persName><name ref="Leo">Leoni</name></persName> qui in his
                        actis interfuit. Signum m(anus) <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Christofalus">Cristofali</name></persName> de
                            <placeName>Clausiano</placeName> qui interfuit. Signum m(anus) <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Stephanus">Stephano</name></persName> de ipso
                        loco qui interfuit. Signum m(anus) <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Vitalianus">Vitaliani</name></persName> filio quondam
                                <persName><name ref="Constantinus">Constantini</name></persName> qui
                        interfuit. Signum m(anus) <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Lupus"
                                >Luponi</name></persName> qui interfuit. Signum m(anus) <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name>Peredeo</name></persName> qui in hac causa
                        interfuit. † Ego <persName key="#Notary #Writer"><name ref="Martinus"
                                >Martinus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>
                        <rs key="#Pagus">pago</rs> territorio <placeName
                            key="#Notary #Writer #Pagus" ref="#places/">Persecetano</placeName> in
                        parte in his actis interfui et hunc brevem <rs key="#Writer"
                        >scripsi</rs>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
